race.description: Join The Club Become A Member Maiden
race.comment: CALATHINITE (8) landed midfield and ran on strongly over 1100m on debut, finishing 1.9L off the winner. This is an easier race today and he'll take plenty of benefit from the debut performance. Draws the inside and can shed the maiden tag today. BRAVE APACHE (1) is first-up today and has trialled well since arriving from Victoria. The gear changes suggest they've hit the reset button on the 5YO who had plenty of chances over in the East. Looks a different commodity now however and he can run a bold race first-up. TANGO RHYTHM (10) showed some talent as a 2YO last campaign, tackling a strong race at Bunbury through the winter. Nice trial in readiness for this and Faithfull takes the ride. A win wouldn't surprise. CRASHED AND BURNED (5) was very good here first-up and can improve on that performance. LADY COCO (4) is better than she showed last time out and can return on a positive note.
